						               													<description>Sylaby is an educational game for children, helping to learn to read using syllables. &amp;#10;The game has 2 decks of cards. One with syllables, the other one with consonants. &amp;#10;In a basic game, every player is given 5 cards, the rest in a drawpile. We open one card and players starts a game. In his turn, a player can either put a card on top of the open card, as long as he is creating a proper word. If he can't or doesn't want, he needs to draw a card. Winner is a player, who will get rid of his/her cards first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The advanced variant introduces the second deck of cards. The rules are the same, but players are making more one syllable word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cards can also be used as a help for recognizing letters and used to introduce children to reading.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
